[[File:Romanian MIM-23 HAWK.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[MIM-23 Hawk]] missile system.]]
The '''61st Anti-aircraft Missiles Regiment "Pelindava"''' (''Regimentul 61 Rachete Antiaeriene'') is an [[air defense]] regiment of the [[Romanian Land Forces]]. Its headquarters are located in [[Slobozia]]. The regiment was part of the [[6th Anti-aircraft Missiles Brigade (Romania)|6th Anti-aircraft Missile Brigade]], which was disbanded in 2006, due to a reorganization process of the Romanian Land Forces. Later on, it was part of the 53rd Anti-Aircraft Missiles Regiment subordinated to the [[1st Infantry Division (Romania)|1st Infantry Division]]. This unit operated the [[S-75 Dvina|S-75 "Volhov"]] and the modern [[MIM-23 Hawk]] [[surface-to-air missile]] systems. 

The main units of the regiment were the 1st Anti-aircraft Missiles Battalion and the 2nd Anti-aircraft Missiles Battalion ''Pelendava'' [http://www.expomil.ro/upload/230.pdf]{{dead link|date=September 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. When Romania's divisions were reorganized and the [[2nd Infantry Division (Romania)|2nd Infantry Division]] was created from units previously belonging to the 1st and 2nd divisions, the ''Pelendava'' Battalion was raised to a regiment and kept with the 1st Division, while the 1st Anti-aircraft Missiles Battalion was transferred to the 2nd Division.

