{{italic title}} '''''A Fada Oriana''''' ({{OCLC|4063855}}), [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] for ''The Fairy [[Oriana]]'', is one of the most emblematic [[Children's literature|children's book]] of [[Portuguese literature]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Otto Coelho|first1=Sara|title=A Menina do Mar e a Fada Oriana chegam ao Panteão|url=http://observador.pt/2014/07/02/poetisa-que-entrou-na-literatura-infantil-para-acalmar-os-filhos-com-sarampo/|website=[[Observador]]|accessdate=15 July 2015|date=2014-07-02|quote=A Menina do Mar e A Fada Oriana são [...] os mais icónicos (''A Menina do Mar'' and ''A Fada Oriana'' are [...] the most iconic [...])|language=Portuguese}}</ref> written in 1958 by [[Sophia de Mello Breyner Andresen]].
The main character is a [[fairy]] who was given the responsibility of ensuring the well-being of a [[forest]] and its inhabitants, the animals and plants. After a while, Oriana befriends a nefarious fish, and while contemplating her image reflected in the river, Oriana is mesmerized by the fish. Deceived by the words of this fish, Oriana ends up neglecting and abandoning the forest, with serious consequences for its denizens. Deprived of her powers as punishment for this failure, Oriana begins a journey of self-consciousness to repair the evils caused by her omission.
The book is a subject on Portuguese Language teaching curricula.<ref>{{cite web |title=MEC associa-se à homenagem a Sophia de Mello Breyner Andresen |url=http://www.portugal.gov.pt/pt/os-ministerios/ministerio-da-educacao-e-ciencia/mantenha-se-atualizado/20140702-mec-sophia.aspx|website=Governo de Portugal |publisher=[[Ministry of Education and Science (Portugal)]] |accessdate=15 July 2015 |language=Portuguese |date=2014-07-02 |quote=No Ensino Básico, a lista de autores e textos portugueses acolhe, a título de exemplo, «A fada Oriana»}}</ref> It has been adapted to [[children's theatre]] several times,<ref>{{cite web |title=O mundo mágico da Fada Oriana |url=http://www.publico.pt/culturaipsilon/noticia/o-mundo-magico-da-fada-oriana-1187835 |website=Público |publisher=[[Público (Portugal)|Público]] |accessdate=15 July 2015 |language=Portuguese |date=2004-03-06 |quote="A Fada Oriana" sobe hoje à cena pela mão da Academia Contemporânea do Espectáculo/[[Teatro do Bolhão]], no Porto.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title="A Fada Oriana" esta tarde no centro cultural de Campo Maior|url=http://www.radioelvas.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=23074:qa-fada-orianaq-esta-tarde-no-centro-cultural-de-campo-maior&catid=1:regional&Itemid=25|website=Rádio Elvas|publisher=radioelvas.com|accessdate=15 July 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref> and has inspired derived works of illustration<ref>{{cite web |title = A Fada Oriana |url = http://marianabaldaia.com/A-Fada-Oriana |publisher = ESAP - [[Escola Superior Artística do Porto]], Guimarães |accessdate = 15 July 2015 |language = Portuguese |date = February 2011 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150715115641/http://marianabaldaia.com/A-Fada-Oriana |archivedate = 15 July 2015 |df = }}</ref> and animation.<ref>{{cite web |title=Oriana |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NG8fsoiaB20 |publisher=Kara Miranda Lawrence, Canada |accessdate=15 January 2015 |language=English |date=April 2009}}</ref>
