'''Bertrange communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Bertrange}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Bertrange]], in south-western [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of eleven members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web|url=http://www.bertrange.lu/vie_politique/ |title=Conseil communal |accessdate=2008-02-05 |date= |publisher=Commune of Bertrange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080118133311/http://www.bertrange.lu/vie_politique/ |archivedate=2008-01-18 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Democratic Party (Luxembourg)|Democratic Party]] (DP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the DP rules outright, under the leadership of [[Mayor of Bertrange|mayor]] [[Paul Geimer]].<ref name="Conseil communal" />
