{{no footnotes|date=May 2017}}
'''CEDAC''' (Centre d'Etude et de Developpement Agricole Cambodgien/Cambodian Center for Study and Development in Agriculture) is an agricultural and rural development organization set up in August 1997 to work for the development of ecologically based family agriculture, and to promote a cooperative and mutual assistance movement in the rural areas of [[Cambodia]]. Initial support came from the [[France|French]] [[non-governmental organization]] (NGO), GRET ([[Groupe de Recherches et d'Echanges Technologiques]]).

