{{Infobox person | name = Elżbieta Barszczewska | image = Elżbieta Barszczewska foto (cropped).jpg | birth_date = {{birth date|df=y|1913|11|29}} | birth_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Congress Poland]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=y|1987|10|14|1913|11|29}} | death_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]] | restingplace = [[Powązki Cemetery]] | spouse = [[Marian Wyrzykowski]] | children = [[Juliusz Wyrzykowski]] | years active = 1934-1981 }}
'''Elżbieta Maria Barszczewska-Wyrzykowska''' (29 November 1913 – 14 October 1987) was a Polish stage and film actress.
After graduating [[Państwowy Instytut Sztuki Teatralnej]], she debuted in [[Polish Theatre in Warsaw]] in 1934. She also starred in several movie roles, including 13 major ones. In [[occupied Poland]], she took part in the activities of the underground theater. After the war she resumed work with the Polish Theater and the [[National Theatre, Warsaw|National Theatre]]. She was a mother of [[Juliusz Wyrzykowski]].
