The '''Gambia Party for Democracy and Progress (GPDP)''' is a small political party in [[the Gambia]]. It is led by [[Henry Gomez]], a resident of [[Hamburg]], [[Germany]]. The party initially launched Gomez as their presidential candidate for the 2006 elections, but after his candidature was refused by the IEC the party joined the UDP/NRP alliance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200609010896.html |title=Gambia: Three Opposition Parties Enlarge Alliance |website=allAfrica |date=1 September 2006}}</ref> The GPDP was part of the opposition [[Coalition 2016]] for the [[Gambian presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]], where [[Adama Barrow]] was selected as the opposition candidate and subsequently won.

