{{Infobox Airline | airline = SonAir | logo = SonAir logo.png | logo_size = 158 | fleet_size = 42 | destinations = 7 | IATA = - | ICAO = SOR | callsign = SONAIR | company_slogan = "Wings of Tranquility" | founded = February 16, 1998 | headquarters = [[Luanda]], [[Angola]] | hubs = [[Quatro de Fevereiro Airport]] | secondary_hubs = | focus_cities = | frequent_flyer = | lounge = | alliance = | website = {{URL|http://www.sonair.co.ao}} }} '''SonAir Airline Services, S.A.''' ({{lang-pt|SonAir Serviço Aéreo, S.A.}}), commonly known as '''SonAir''', is a venture of the [[Angola]]n national petroleum company [[Sonangol Group]]. It provides helicopter services to Angolan oil facilities, both onshore and offshore, as well as scheduled and charter services within Africa and to the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=China Sonangol International Airlines |url=http://centreforaviation.com/profiles/airlines/china-sonangol-international-airlines-sor |publisher=CAPA Centre for Aviation |accessdate=24 February 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301053840/http://centreforaviation.com/profiles/airlines/china-sonangol-international-airlines-sor |archivedate=March 1, 2014 }}</ref>
Domestically they also provide air transportation to several business groups - private and government, outside the oil business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.planespotters.net/Airline/China-Sonangol-International|title=China Sonangol International Fleet Details and History|website=www.planespotters.net|language=en|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> The company is also the first to provide direct transportation of passengers and cargo between [[Angola]] and the [[United States]]. Until 2018, the airline provided thrice-weekly services between [[Luanda]] (LAD) and [[George Bush Intercontinental Airport|Houston]] (IAH) utilizing a [[Boeing 747-400]] (10 First Class, 143 Business Class, some of which were marketed as a [[Premium economy|Premium Economy]] with a lesser amenity service, and 36 Economy Class seats) operated by [[Atlas Air]].{{citation needed|date=February 2014}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atlasair.com/holdings/archive.asp?Pressid=10787|title=Atlas Air Worldwide Holdings|website=www.atlasair.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>
